NotifyOnLoginHelpText.message: If this module is incomplete or has relevant messages send a notification when you login to a character.

NotifyOnZoneChangeHelpText.message: If this module is incomplete or has relevant messages send a notification when you change zones.

FeaturesTabDescription.message: Main features of DailyDuty to add QoL

DebugTabString.message: Settings for debugging or showing more information

TasksTabDescription.message: View and configure daily and weekly tasks

TimersTabDescription.message: View time until various daily and weekly tasks reset

DutyRouletteDutyFinderOverlayAutomationI.message: The 'Duty Roulette' status is gathered directly from internal game data and will always be precisely in sync with the game.

DutyRouletteDutyFinderOverlayInformation.message: Requires task module 'Duty Roulette' to be enabled to function

DutyRouletteDutyFinderOverlayDescription.message: Changes the colors of the 'Duty Roulette' text in the Duty Finder to reflect the daily completion status.

DutyRouletteDutyFinderOverlayTechnicalDe.message:
Use the 'Duty Roulette' module to configure which roulettes are colored.

You can also set the 'complete' and 'incomplete' colors in the 'Duty Roulette' module

Roulettes that are not tracked will not be colored, regardless of their completion status.

WondrousTailsDutyFinderOverlayDescriptio.message:
Adds a clover icon next to the duties in the Duty Finder, if that duty is in your Wondrous Tails book.

The clover will be golden if that duty is able to be completed to reward you a stamp.

The clover will be hollow if that duty has already been claimed for a stamp.

WondrousTailsDutyFinderOverlayAutomation.message:
The Wondrous Tails duties are read directly from game data.

The Duty Finder may need to be opened and closed again to refresh the displayed data.

WondrousTailsDutyFinderOverlayTechnicalD.message: The game code will not clear the task's data when you complete your book for the week. This will cause the Duty Finder to reflect the status of the last obtained book.

TodoWindowInformation.message: The Todo window is a small window that shows your tracked tasks. This window is helpful for figuring out what you still need to do at a quick glance.

TimersWindowEnableTimersWarning.message: Enable which timers you would like to see here in 'Timers Window Configuration'

TimersWindowInformation.message: The timers window allows you to view the time until various resets as a handy user interface element.

NoSelectionInformation.message: Select an item to configure in the left pane

NotificationsThrottleDescription.message:
This setting controls the frequency of chat notifications from DailyDuty.

Default: 5 Minutes

NotificationsDelayDescription.message: Prevents notifications from showing until after the selected weekday. The start of the week is 'Tuesday'

DutyRouletteInformation.message:
The Duty Roulette is a daily task that awards experience and gil once a day per completion.

Additional rewards such as various tomestones and grand company seals are rewarded depending on roulette type and level of job you queue as.

DutyRouletteAutomationInformation.message:
This module is entirely automatic, no user interaction is required.

The completion status of each roulette is gathered directly from the game's data.

DutyRouletteTechnicalInformation.message:
You can configure this module to alert you when specified duties have not yet been completed today.

Only the duties selected for tracking in the Options tab will give notifications.

Some listed roulettes may not be available due to not being unlocked or due to being unavailable until a later patch. It is not recommended to track roulettes you do not have access to.

DutyRouletteClickableLinkDescription.message: Notifications can be clicked on to open the Duty Finder

DutyRouletteExpandedInfo.message: Displays individual incomplete duties in the todo window.

WondrousTailsInformation.message:
Wondrous Tails is a level 60 weekly activity that allows players to complete old content to earn rewards. With some randomized elements, Wondrous Tails is an interesting way to revisit these older duties every week.

Weekly rewards include half of a level worth's of experience to whichever job turns in the book, and selectable rewards such as tomestones or MGP vouchers.

WondrousTailsAutomationInformation.message: Wondrous Tails data is extracted directly from the game's data, and will always be in sync with the current status of your book. No user interaction is required to keep this data synchronized.

WondrousTailsTechnicalDescription.message:
The game code will not clear the Wondrous Tails data when you complete your book, even if you turn it in without 9 stamps.

This module will only consider a Wondrous Tails book complete once you have 9 stamps placed.

WondrousTailsOpenBookClickableLinkDescri.message: Notifications can be clicked on to open your Wondrous Tails book

WondrousTailsUnavailableMessage.message: This instance is available for a stamp if you re-roll it

WondrousTailsAvailableMessage.message: A stamp is already available for this instance

WondrousTailsCompletableMessage.message: Completing this instance will reward you with a stamp

WondrousTailsClaimableMessage.message: You can claim a stamp for the last instance

WondrousTailsInstanceNotificationsDescri.message:
Send notifications at the start of a duty, if that duty is a part of your Wondrous Tails book
Additionally, it will send notifications after completing a duty, reminding you to collect your stamp

WondrousTailsStickerAvailableNotificatio.message: Send a notification on zone change if any tasks in your book are currently available to claim a sticker.

TreasureMapInformation.message:
Treasure Maps are gatherable items with the Disciples of Land jobs once every 18 hours. These maps can be opened as part of a mini-event for various rewards. Alternatively, these maps can be sold on the market board.

You can only hold one of each type of map at a time.

TreasureMapAutomationInformation.message: Treasure map data is gathered by reading chat information when the treasure map is gathered. If DailyDuty was installed after you have collected a map, you must wait until you are able to collect another map for the tracking to begin.

TreasureMapReSyncInformation.message: You can force a re-sync of Treasure Map by opening the 'Timers' menu

BeastTribeInformation.message: Beast Tribes are a daily task that can be completed for experience rewards and to earn progress towards beast tribes affiliations that will unlock unique dyes, glamours, mounts, and housing items.

BeastTribeAutomationInformation.message: Beast tribe allowance information is extracted directly from the game's data and will always be in sync with the current status of the game.

BeastTribeTechnicalInformation.message:
DailyDuty provides options to alert you when you are at a threshold of allowances, either by directly imputing the threshold, or by specifying how many beast tribes-worth of allowances you wish to track.

Upon reaching a new tier in each beast tribe you get 3 additional allowances for that tribe, DailyDuty is unable to track this information and will not consider the extra allowances for tracking purposes.

LevequestInformation.message: Levequests are repeatable quests players can perform to earn experience, gil and items. Unlike regular quests, which can only be performed once per character, levequests can be repeated as long as the player has Leve allowances.

LevequestAutomationInformation.message: Levequest information is extracted directly from the game's data and will always be in sync with the current status of the game.

LevequestTechnicalInformation.message: Once a levequest is accepted the allowance is spent, if you cancel the levequest the allowance is not returned.

MiniCactpotInformation.message: Mini Cactpot is a daily scratch-card like activity you can do three times per day. Each Mini Cactpot ticket awards a various amount of MGP up to 10,000 MGP per ticket.

MiniCactpotAutomationInformation.message: Tracking is done by monitoring the opening of the Mini Cactpot ticket. If DailyDuty was installed after you have completed your daily Mini Cactpot, it will not be tracked.

MiniCactpotTechnicalInformation.message: The game removes your Mini Cactpot ticket allowance when the window is opened and you spend the MGP to purchase the ticket. If your game is closed or crashes after the ticket window opened, that ticket will be lost.

MiniCactpotClickableLinkDescription.message: Notifications can be clicked on to teleport to the Gold Saucer

MiniCactpotReSyncInformation.message: You can force a re-sync of Mini Cactpot allowances by speaking to the 'Mini Cactpot Broker' and selecting 'Purchase a Mini Cactpot ticket'

CustomDeliveryInformation.message: Custom Deliveries is a weekly DoH/DoL task you can complete for various crafting or gathering scripts, exp rewards, various materia, folklore tomes, and more.

CustomDeliveryAutomationInformation.message: Custom Delivery information is gathered directly from the game's data, and will always be in sync with the current status of the game.

DomanEnclaveInformation.message: The Doman Enclave is a weekly task you can complete for gil rewards. You donate junk items in exchange for a multiple of their value in gil back, resulting in profit. The reward multiplier increases higher the more you progress through the Doman Enclave.

DomanEnclaveAutomationInformation.message: Doman Enclave data is tracked automatically, but only while you are actually in the Doman Enclave area.

DomanEnclaveTechnicalInformation.message: Once you visit the Doman Enclave, DailyDuty attempts to keep a copy of the status, and will reset that status at the start of a new week. If the data somehow becomes out of sync, simply re-visit the Doman Enclave and it will automatically re-sync.

DomanEnclaveClickableLinkDescription.message: Notifications can be clicked on to teleport to the Doman Enclave

DomanEnclaveInitializationWarning.message: You can re-sync Doman Enclave data by visiting the Doman Enclave

FashionReportInformation.message: Fashion Report is a weekly task you can complete for MGP. Simply 'Present yourself for judging' once a week without any effort and be rewarded with 10,000 MGP. You can attempt to create an outfit for a higher score, additional MGP, and titles.

FashionReportAutomationInformation.message: Fashion Report data is collected when you present yourself for judging. The current high score and allowances remaining is extracted from the UI when the judging is complete.

FashionReportTechnicalInformation.message:
Data is collected both when you interact with 'Masked Rose' and when you are actually presenting yourself for judging. This should keep the data in sync with the game data at all times.

Fashion Report status will show as 'Complete' while Fashion Report is unavailable, and 'Incomplete' once it is available or the completion conditions are not met.

FashionReportSingleModeDescription.message: Only notify if no allowances have been spent this week and Fashion Report is available for turn-in

FashionReportEightyPlusDescription.message: Notify if any allowances remain this week, the highest score is below 80 and Fashion Report is available for turn-in

FashionReportAllDescription.message: Notify if any allowances remain this week and fashion report is available for turn-in

FashionReportClickableLinkDescription.message: Notifications can be clicked on to teleport to the Gold Saucer

FashionReportReSyncInformation.message: You can re-sync Fashion Report data by speaking to 'Masked Rose'

JumboCactpotInformation.message: Jumbo Cactpot is a weekly task where you can purchase 3 lottery tickets. These tickets allow you to pick any 4-digit number you wish, and depending on how many numbers are matched at the drawing the following week, you can earn MGP.

JumboCactpotAutomationInformation.message: Jumbo Cactpot data is collected when you purchase your tickets. If DailyDuty was not installed when you purchased your tickets it will be unable to track your tickets for that week.

JumboCactpotTechnicalInformation.message:
While DailyDuty displays the value of the tickets collected, the only information needed to track the status is how many tickets have been purchased.

Upon weekly reset the stored tickets will be removed and you will be prompted to purchase new tickets. If you have any pending rewards, you will have to collect your tickets in order to purchase new tickets.

Due to how the fallback re-sync system works, if you speak to the 'Jumbo Cactpot Broker' before collecting your rewards, last-weeks tickets will get re-logged and the task will be marked as complete. Speaking to the 'Jumbo Cactpot Broker' after collecting your rewards will re-sync the status back to incomplete.

JumboCactpotClickableLinkDescription.message: Notifications can be clicked on to teleport to the Gold Saucer

JumboCactpotReSyncInformation.message: You can force a re-sync of ticket data by speaking to the 'Jumbo Cactpot Broker'

HuntMarksWeeklyInformation.message:
Weekly Hunts are also know as 'Elite Hunts', these are Weekly Hunts you can do for various hunt currencies such as Allied Seals, Centurio Seals, and Sacks of Nuts.

These currencies can be exchanged for various rewards. A reward that is of note is the Aetheryte Tickets, which can be used instead of paying gil for aetheryte teleports.

HuntMarksAutomationInformation.message: Hunt data is tracked by observing changes in the games stored data. If DailyDuty was not installed when you obtained a hunt mark then it can not be tracked correctly.

HuntMarksTechnicalInformation.message:
While the data is always in sync with the game, the game does not clear this data on reset. Instead, it only clears the data when you pick up the new hunt mark item.

DailyDuty will reset its copy of the tracked data each week and attempt to start tracking when a new hunt mark is picked up.

HuntMarksDailyInformation.message: Daily Hunts are low rank hunts that are available each day. These hunts involve killing a specific number of fairly common enemies.
